This project is coded for checking  Failed logs by finding "Failed password".
The result is: if one IP had more than 5 failed logs, it will be displayed with amount of unsuccessful tries.
If there were no IP the line from logs will be written to skipped lines which will be displazed and can be checked.

How to run code:
Usage: python3 main.py <path_to_log>

How result supposed to look like:
IP: 100.10.100.10 | failed attempts: 18
IP: 200.20.200.20 | failed attempts: 7
Suspected line:  2026-07-09T10:00:00.000000+02:00 PC_NAME sshd-session[999]: Failed password for invalid user SuperAdmin
Suspected line:  2026-07-09T10:00:00.000000+02:00 PC_NAME sshd-session[999]: Failed password for invalid user SuperAdmin
Suspected line:  2026-07-09T10:00:00.000000+02:00 PC_NAME sshd-session[999]: Failed password for invalid user SuperAdmin
Suspected line:  2026-07-09T10:00:00.000000+02:00 PC_NAME sshd-session[999]: Failed password for invalid user SuperAdmin
Suspected line:  2026-07-09T10:00:00.000000+02:00 PC_NAME sshd-session[999]: Failed password for invalid user SuperAdmin
Suspected line:  2026-07-09T10:00:00.000000+02:00 PC_NAME sshd-session[999]: Failed password for invalid user SuperAdmin


